reviewText: Weeks 4, 5 and 6 were not interesting, and lecturers did not have the level of the other lecturers from the course.

There were some great discussions and topics involved in this course, however it did not feel as well put together as others in the specialisation. Two out of 6 weeks focussed on branding and marketing and felt particularly out of place for people looking at learning more about HR, OD and leadership.For example, there is a lot of information out there about metaphor and how we relate to the world around us (Lakoff and Johnson, for a start) that may have been more appropriate and effective. If you are mostly attracted to this course because of the nature of 'meaning-making' then I suggest you explore those deep resources first.
